cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SE

The paper discusses a new type of blockchain that aims to improve performance, decentralization, and flexibility without compromising security. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SE (Software Engineering). However, given the focus on security and consensus algorithms, cs.CR is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also possible because the paper discusses issues related to distributed systems, data structures, and software engineering.
